-- Polish Opposition Party Won’t Join Coalition, Gazeta Reports
-- B y   K a t y a   A n d r u s z
-- 2012-02-22T07:39:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/polish-opposition-party-won-t-join-coalition-gazeta-reports.html
Poland ’s  Palikot Movement , which won
10 percent in last year’s general election, will not join the
ruling coalition of Prime Minister Donald Tusk,  Gazeta Wyborcza 
reported, citing leader Janusz Palikot.  “We want Tusk to carry on suffering” with its junior
coalition partner the Peasants’ Party, Palikot said in an
interview with the newspaper, published today.  Poland’s parliamentary term is due to last until late 2015.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katya Andrusz in Warsaw at 
 kandrusz@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  